Package gov.nyc.doitt.gis.geoclient.service.search

Class InputValue

java.lang.Object
gov.nyc.doitt.gis.geoclient.service.search.InputValue
public class InputValue extends Object
Value class used to retain metadata about values used to create search request arguments. Specifically, this class tracks whether an input value originated from the parser (ValueSource.PARSED) verbatim, was from the parser but mapped to another value (ValueSource.MAPPED) or was assigned by the search because it was missing (ValueSource.ASSIGNED). Classification of ValueSource is based on which constructor was used to create this instance. This class also tracks whether the value is considered to be resolved (e.g. usable as a search argument) based on the following criteria:
  • If this object is not ValueSource.MAPPED, it is considered resolved.
  • If this object is ValueSource.MAPPED and the mappedValue is not null, it is considered resolved.
  • If this object is ValueSource.MAPPED and the mappedValue is null, it is considered unresolved.
